SIMPLE: usurer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Usurer
<hw>U"su*rer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>usurier</ets>, LL. <ets>usurarius</ets>. See <er>Usury</er>, and
cf. <er>Usurarious</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who lends money and takes interest for it; a
money lender.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If thou lend money to any of my people that is poor by thee, thou
shalt not be to him as a <qex>usurer</qex>, neither shalt thou lay upon
him usury.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xxii. 25.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who lends money at a rate of interest beyond
that established by law; one who exacts an exorbitant rate of interest
for the use of money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was wont to call me <qex>usurer</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usurious</ent>⟦br⟧
